Cut bread diagonally into 1-1/2-in. slices to within 1/2 in. of bottom. Repeat cuts in opposite direction. Cut cheese into 1-in. squares. Place one cheese square and one mushroom if desired into each slit. Combine butter and garlic powder; spoon over the bread. Place on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes or until cheese is melted.